This paper deals with tracing and explaining the execution of CLP(FD) programs, which falls under the area of constraint programming. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of filtering algorithms for global constraints, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with the design of the trace structure, which involves logical reasoning and deduction, making cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) a possible sub-category. The paper also discusses the representation and identification of different entities, which falls under the area of software engineering, making cs.SE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the use of nested block structures, which is a common technique in data structures, making cs.DS a possible sub-category.
